</span><span class=\"ju-examples\" style=\"color:#552656;font-family:tahoma;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, Ms. Esprit is an annoying person who is disliked by most of the neighbors.</span></p>"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":1,"hideRightPanel":0,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":"0","audioPath":"9"},"rightText":"<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"ju-tableplain ju-tight\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><tbody><tr><td><p><span class=\"ju-labels\" style=\"color:#59595B;font-family:tahoma;font-weight:bold;\">Mr. Aplomb&#39;s counter-rebuttal</span></p><p>The noise from Ms. Esprit&#39;s house occurred after midnight on a Thursday and at 2:00 a.m. on a Saturday, so the noise ordinance supports my argument.&nbsp; Furthermore, Ms. Esprit&#39;s enjoyment of her property shouldn&#39;t be allowed to interfere with my enjoyment of my property.&nbsp; While it may be&nbsp;true that having fun decreases stress, other authorities state that listening to excessive noise raises stress levels,&nbsp;as well as interfering&nbsp; with sleep.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","leftText":"<p>An effective counter-rebuttal addresses as many weaknesses in the rebuttal as possible.&nbsp; It is possible to challenge the rebuttal&#39;s facts, logic, or expert opinion, or any other ways the rebuttal is weak.<br />&nbsp;</p>","headerText":"Putting it all together"},{"settings":{"showAudio":1,"showNext":1,"showHeader":0,"hideRightPanel":1,"delayStep":0,"delayRight":0,"audioPath":"10"},"leftText":"<p>Most arguments do not take place in a courtroom, but a court case illustrates the process of making an argument and defending it.&nbsp; So, when you make an argument, think about how another person could rebut what you are arguing.&nbsp; Answering this person with an effective counter-rebuttal will make your whole argument stronger. &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>","rightText":null}],"overviewHeader":"Overview"}
